commit.message: Add pool for background thread to stop leaking.
Use exisiting CFLAGS and CMAKE_OPTIONS variables.
No, it's not true. This is true history.
Make both armv6, armv7 binary. Xcode4 requires them.
FIX: cmake 2.8.4 on x86_64 raises error.
It was for iOS SDK 4.1, actually.
Rename Icon, Move source assets into Assets folder.
Use the latest version of iOS SDK.
Bump SDK version up to 4.1, Update options of build script.
Use lapack in Accelerate.framework insted of the one build from OpenCV 3rdparty code.
Update OpenCV to 2.1, Update build script
FIX: cpp-4.2 responed error on Snow Leopard
Add min-version flag to select correct libs
Add missing additional header files from OpenCV 2.0
Change path of precompiled opencv libraries

Update merged configure script for newer version of SDK

Remove old separated configure script

Add experimental merged configure tool command

It may not work with current 3.x SDKs...

Add license file

These source code are under MIT license.

FIX: error with OpenCV for MacOS X

 * Static link version of OpenCV (compiled)
   * get source from CVS
   * cd cvs_head
   * patch -p0 < ../opencv_build_scripts/cv.h.patch
   * mkdir build
   * edit opencv_build_scripts/*.sh for your enviroment(--prefix etc...)
   * pushd build; ../../opencv_build_scripts/configure.sh; make; make install; popd
